WEBVTT

00:07.529 --> 00:08.965
Kevin and Allison --
together forever!

00:09.096 --> 00:11.228
Oh!Aah!

00:11.359 --> 00:13.535
So what'd I miss?Allison:
I'm gonna kill Kevin.

00:13.665 --> 00:14.840
You know any
natural-born killers?

00:14.971 --> 00:15.885
I think I might.

00:16.016 --> 00:17.974
Okay, I can do it.

00:18.105 --> 00:19.802
[Glass shatters]Is that a gun?

00:19.932 --> 00:20.759
I have to protect us.

00:20.890 --> 00:22.674
[Gasping]

00:22.805 --> 00:24.459
It was Nick.He wasn't supposed to come
for another week.

00:24.589 --> 00:25.851
Oh, trust me, I know.

00:25.982 --> 00:27.940
Aah!We don't take shootings
lightly.

00:28.071 --> 00:28.985
You may not want
to go out of town.

00:29.116 --> 00:30.813
I have a higher callin',
babe.

00:30.943 --> 00:32.249
I'm running for office!

00:32.380 --> 00:34.947
[Cheers and applause]

00:35.078 --> 00:37.298
You're the one who tried to kill
her husband. And it was a bust.

00:37.428 --> 00:38.429
And you're the one
who helped.

00:38.560 --> 00:39.822
[Gasps]

00:39.952 --> 00:42.042
I heard everything.

00:42.172 --> 00:43.304
Neil, it's not
what you think.

00:43.434 --> 00:46.176
[Screaming]
Uh!

00:46.307 --> 00:47.873
Patti: You're not gonna tell
Kevin anything.

00:48.004 --> 00:49.962
♪

00:51.921 --> 00:53.314
[Panting]

00:53.444 --> 00:55.838
[Neil groaning]

00:55.968 --> 00:57.883
♪

00:58.014 --> 00:59.711
Ah. What the hell are you doing?

00:59.842 --> 01:01.278
You were choking her!You were choking me!

01:01.409 --> 01:03.063
I was not. I was trying
to get my phone back.

01:03.193 --> 01:04.325
You had your hands
on my neck!

01:04.455 --> 01:05.717
What the hell
were you thinking?

01:05.848 --> 01:08.155
Oh, what? C-Come on.

01:08.285 --> 01:10.679
She's trying to
play victim here?

01:10.809 --> 01:12.898
You tried to kill Kevin.

01:13.029 --> 01:14.509
Kevin! [Scoffs]

01:14.639 --> 01:16.685
You're insane.

01:16.815 --> 01:19.514
Everyone has to know.
Kevin has to know.

01:19.644 --> 01:21.559
He has to.

01:21.690 --> 01:23.953
-[Screams]
-Oh, shit!

01:24.084 --> 01:24.954
Allison?

01:25.085 --> 01:26.912
Oh, God.

01:27.043 --> 01:29.611
Oh, God.

01:29.741 --> 01:30.655
Allison?!

01:30.786 --> 01:33.354
Okay, okay.

01:33.484 --> 01:35.747
Allison?Okay.

01:35.878 --> 01:37.271
We have to m-make it look

01:37.401 --> 01:39.186
like none of this
ever happened, okay?

01:39.316 --> 01:40.491
Like normal.

01:40.622 --> 01:42.406
Normal?

01:42.537 --> 01:44.974
But this isn't normal.
None of this is normal.

01:45.105 --> 01:46.410
I didn't know what to do.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.586
So you kettled my brother?
How does this help?

01:48.717 --> 01:49.979
Well, he's
unconscious, right?

01:50.110 --> 01:51.633
Which means
he's not talking.

01:51.763 --> 01:54.375
He's also not moving.
What are we gonna do about this?

01:56.855 --> 01:58.161
Allison, hello?!

01:58.292 --> 01:59.945
I know, I know.

02:00.076 --> 02:01.730
Just please
stop yelling, okay?

02:01.860 --> 02:03.384
[Neil groans]

02:06.343 --> 02:07.866
Okay, I have a plan.
I have a plan.

02:07.997 --> 02:09.172
Give me your phone.

02:09.303 --> 02:10.956
Why?Give me your phone, okay?

02:11.087 --> 02:12.828
♪

02:12.958 --> 02:13.959
Who are you calling?

02:14.090 --> 02:15.526
Why are you still yelling?

02:15.657 --> 02:20.705
♪

02:20.836 --> 02:22.185
Hi!

02:22.316 --> 02:24.448
Hi, hi, hi,
this is Allison.

02:24.579 --> 02:27.625
Fine. Um, listen,
I could really use your help

02:27.756 --> 02:30.193
with...something.

02:32.108 --> 02:33.979
[Groans]

02:34.110 --> 02:36.547
[Duct tape rips]

02:36.678 --> 02:42.031
♪

02:43.641 --> 02:45.556
[Groans]

02:45.600 --> 02:47.254
Hey.

02:47.384 --> 02:49.169
I'm really sorry
about all this.

02:50.953 --> 02:52.041
I know.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.217
[Doorbell ringing]

02:57.394 --> 02:59.701
We'll fix it
together, okay?

02:59.831 --> 03:01.442
All of it.

03:04.619 --> 03:05.837
Okay.[Rapid knocking on door]

03:05.968 --> 03:08.188
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

03:10.146 --> 03:15.630
Oh.[Sighs]

03:15.760 --> 03:17.022
Hey.Whoa.

03:17.153 --> 03:18.763
Thank you.No, I mean hey,

03:18.894 --> 03:20.635
hey, hey, Diane.

03:20.765 --> 03:23.377
I -- You okay?

03:23.507 --> 03:25.248
Fine.

03:25.379 --> 03:27.468
Okay.

03:27.598 --> 03:30.558
Well, thank you
for bringing the hand truck.

03:30.688 --> 03:32.299
Oh.

03:32.429 --> 03:34.518
Mm-hmm.

03:34.649 --> 03:36.694
Okay.

03:36.825 --> 03:38.305
Sure you're okay, D?

03:38.435 --> 03:41.873
Chuck's been cheating on me
for 10 years.

03:42.004 --> 03:46.269
With Tanya Iacono
from across the street.

03:46.400 --> 03:48.663
Oh, D, that --
that is terrible.

03:48.793 --> 03:50.534
I am so sorry.

03:50.665 --> 03:53.058
Am I
that much of an idiot?

03:53.189 --> 03:54.277
[Neil groans]

03:54.408 --> 03:56.105
No, no, no, no.

03:56.236 --> 04:00.501
Sh-She has this curly hair
like Felicity.

04:00.631 --> 04:02.720
[Neil grunting]

04:02.851 --> 04:04.940
And she sells Avon.

04:05.070 --> 04:08.291
Has all those
fancy creams.

04:08.422 --> 04:10.946
But, D, you -- you have
great hair, too, you know?

04:11.076 --> 04:12.687
You're --
You're too good for him.

04:12.817 --> 04:13.949
You're better off
without him,

04:14.079 --> 04:17.213
so just --
just kick him to the curb.

04:17.344 --> 04:18.606
Oh.

04:18.736 --> 04:20.042
Yeah, yeah.

04:21.652 --> 04:23.132
It's fine, it's fine.Yeah.

04:23.263 --> 04:24.438
Just -- to hell with him.

04:24.568 --> 04:25.743
Yeah.
Right?

04:25.874 --> 04:27.484
The jerk can't
even remember to --

04:27.615 --> 04:30.357
to drink water
unless I remind him.

04:30.487 --> 04:31.749
He'll probably drop dead
in a week.

04:31.880 --> 04:33.360
Oh, that's the spirit.

04:33.490 --> 04:34.709
Oh, hey, let's, uh --

04:34.839 --> 04:36.493
let's go down the Seas
for a few, huh?

04:36.624 --> 04:38.278
My treat?[Thud, Neil groans]

04:38.408 --> 04:39.714
Can I get a rain check?

04:39.844 --> 04:43.108
Um, 'cause I've been
moving some furniture.

04:43.239 --> 04:45.894
[Grunts]

04:46.024 --> 04:47.635
Okay.Okay.

04:47.765 --> 04:49.332
♪

04:49.463 --> 04:51.291
Okay, I'll just --Alright.

04:51.421 --> 04:52.422
Bye.

04:55.469 --> 04:57.079
[Neil groans]

05:00.256 --> 05:02.389
You have to
keep him quiet.

05:02.519 --> 05:04.521
I'm sorry, I've never had
a hostage before.

05:04.652 --> 05:06.784
I'm not great at it yet.

05:06.915 --> 05:09.744
I think it's technically
kidnapping, not hostage taking.

05:09.874 --> 05:12.486
Are you serious?[Vehicle approaching]

05:12.616 --> 05:14.792
Oh, no, no, no, no, no,
that's Kevin.

05:14.923 --> 05:16.228
Oh, God.

05:16.359 --> 05:19.144
[Car doors open in distance]

05:19.275 --> 05:21.930
Hmm?

05:22.060 --> 05:23.497
[Both laughing]

05:23.627 --> 05:26.238
Oh, God, what a night!

05:26.369 --> 05:28.850
It's like I was made
for politicking.

05:28.980 --> 05:32.723
It's those meaty mitts.
They're great for handshaking.

05:32.854 --> 05:34.899
I've always been told
I'm ham-handed.

05:34.943 --> 05:37.641
Now I made it a positive.
[ Audience laughing ]

05:37.772 --> 05:39.948
Ah, this belt
is killin' me.

05:39.991 --> 05:42.037
Hey, think about it, though.
[ Audience laughing ]

05:42.167 --> 05:44.561
If you win,
you could make this town

05:44.692 --> 05:46.955
a much better place to live.

05:47.085 --> 05:48.348
For us.

05:48.478 --> 05:49.523
It's true.
Think about it --

05:49.653 --> 05:52.352
parades,
no speeding tickets,

05:52.482 --> 05:54.702
peeing outside any bar
we damn well please!

05:54.745 --> 05:56.704
[ Audience laughing ]

05:56.834 --> 05:57.879
[Grunting]

05:58.009 --> 05:59.881
Hey! We have to
get him out of here.

06:00.011 --> 06:01.361
Oh, yeah.

06:01.491 --> 06:04.276
♪

06:04.407 --> 06:06.801
That's it. I think
this new City Councilman

06:06.931 --> 06:08.193
has earned himself a beer.

06:08.324 --> 06:10.065
No, hey --

06:10.195 --> 06:11.545
-Oh --
-[Grunts]

06:11.675 --> 06:12.850
[Whispering]
Lift with your legs.

06:12.981 --> 06:14.025
[Whispering] Lift at all.

06:14.156 --> 06:15.679
I am.Come on.

06:15.810 --> 06:18.856
We got to focus.
This thing isn't yours yet.

06:18.987 --> 06:21.119
They're picking the candidate
this week.

06:21.250 --> 06:23.774
So step one -- we got to
get your name out there.

06:23.905 --> 06:26.081
Hmm.
Oh, I still got that bullhorn.

06:26.211 --> 06:27.996
Remember when we protested
the grand opening

06:28.126 --> 06:31.652
of that new vegan
barbecue place? Ugh!

06:31.782 --> 06:35.133
No, we're gonna go
full "Mad Men" on this.

06:35.264 --> 06:38.223
We're gonna come up with
an incredible TV ad campaign

06:38.267 --> 06:40.878
and day drink.
[ Audience laughing ]

06:41.009 --> 06:42.445
We have two days.

06:42.576 --> 06:44.273
[Grunts]

06:45.666 --> 06:48.016
You mean like an adad?

06:48.146 --> 06:50.714
Yes.Something awesome?

06:50.845 --> 06:51.933
Like my very own...

06:52.063 --> 06:54.849
♪ Maybe it's Maybelline ♪

06:54.979 --> 06:56.938
But tougher?

06:57.068 --> 06:58.200
No!

06:58.330 --> 07:00.942
Hell yes.
I'm Kevin McRoberts,

07:01.072 --> 07:03.771
and I approve that message!

07:03.814 --> 07:06.077
[ Audience laughing ]

07:06.208 --> 07:08.384
Thin much? [Laughs]

07:08.428 --> 07:09.820
[ Audience laughs, applauds ]

07:09.951 --> 07:16.610
♪

07:16.740 --> 07:18.786
Okay.

07:18.916 --> 07:19.743
Okay what?

07:19.874 --> 07:21.049
What are we gonna --

07:21.179 --> 07:22.354
How we gonna
deal with this?

07:22.485 --> 07:23.486
How's he gonna
go to the bathroom?

07:23.617 --> 07:25.009
I don't know yet.

07:25.140 --> 07:27.664
♪

07:27.795 --> 07:29.884
He knows. Everything.

07:30.014 --> 07:30.928
No, he doesn't
know everything.

07:31.059 --> 07:32.713
And Nick is alive.

07:32.843 --> 07:34.671
This whole thing, when it was
just the two of us,

07:34.802 --> 07:35.933
I-I don't know.

07:36.064 --> 07:38.980
It seemed reasonable,
justifiable.

07:39.110 --> 07:40.372
But it wasn't,
and it's not.

07:40.503 --> 07:42.505
He knows, Allison,
and now he's tied up

07:42.636 --> 07:43.854
and bleeding,
and we did that, too.

07:43.985 --> 07:45.073
Okay. Okay.

07:45.203 --> 07:47.292
Look, this is bad.

07:47.423 --> 07:48.729
It is.

07:48.859 --> 07:50.339
But at least we bought
ourselves some time.

07:50.470 --> 07:52.472
[Neil groans]Hey? We'll figure it out.

07:52.602 --> 07:55.997
♪

07:56.127 --> 07:58.129
I just...

07:58.260 --> 07:59.827
need some more time.

07:59.957 --> 08:08.879
♪

08:09.010 --> 08:18.280
♪

08:18.410 --> 08:27.550
♪

08:27.681 --> 08:28.551
Oh, God.

08:28.682 --> 08:29.770
What time is it?

08:29.900 --> 08:31.946
I have no idea.

08:32.076 --> 08:34.731
Can't tell if it's been
20 minutes or 8 hours.

08:34.862 --> 08:35.776
Oh, God.

08:35.906 --> 08:38.779
Oh, no,
Kevin must be up by now.

08:38.909 --> 08:39.867
Ugh.

08:39.997 --> 08:42.260
♪

08:42.391 --> 08:45.176
Ah.

08:45.307 --> 08:47.701
[Grunts]

08:47.831 --> 08:49.354
What are you doing?

08:49.485 --> 08:51.748
I went for a run.

08:51.879 --> 08:54.359
I got up early,
and I went for a run.

08:54.490 --> 08:58.015
♪

08:58.146 --> 08:59.539
You're leaving me here
to deal --

08:59.669 --> 09:01.715
No, no, no, no.
I'll be right back, okay?

09:01.845 --> 09:03.151
I promise.

09:03.281 --> 09:07.024
♪

09:07.155 --> 09:08.635
[Door opens, shuts]

09:08.765 --> 09:10.114
[Footsteps]

09:10.245 --> 09:13.814
♪

09:13.944 --> 09:15.511
[Door opens, shuts]

09:15.642 --> 09:22.213
♪

09:22.344 --> 09:24.433
Finally, you kiss a baby
[smooches]

09:24.564 --> 09:27.567
you dump the baby,
turn to camera,

09:27.697 --> 09:29.177
say you approve
this message

09:29.307 --> 09:31.788
because your name
is Kevin McRoberts.

09:31.832 --> 09:33.877
Boom!
[ Audience laughing ]

09:34.008 --> 09:35.313
I don't know, Dad.

09:35.444 --> 09:38.665
What don't you know?
Well, that's your name, son.

09:38.795 --> 09:41.232
I know, but this ad has --
has no pomp,

09:41.363 --> 09:44.018
It has no whimsy.

09:44.148 --> 09:46.194
A-And you did
all these drawings?

09:46.324 --> 09:48.326
Yeah.Dad, they're terrible.

09:48.370 --> 09:49.893
[ Audience laughing ]

09:50.024 --> 09:52.243
Look, this town has to believe
you're a serious candidate.

09:52.374 --> 09:54.202
Serious candidate?

09:54.332 --> 09:57.509
Dad, the only thing serious
about me is my heart condition.

09:57.553 --> 09:58.859
[ Audience laughing ]

09:58.989 --> 10:01.078
[Panting]

10:01.209 --> 10:03.864
I went for a run.

10:03.994 --> 10:05.387
How many miles?

10:05.517 --> 10:06.693
Two.

10:06.736 --> 10:08.477
Hmm.
[ Audience laughing ]

10:08.608 --> 10:10.131
But, hey, I'm glad
that you're here,

10:10.261 --> 10:11.872
because now you can hear
the new jingle

10:12.002 --> 10:14.222
that I wrote for the campaign.
[Clears throat]

10:14.352 --> 10:16.485
♪ Ke-- No.

10:16.616 --> 10:19.096
Kev, we got to
get this right.

10:19.227 --> 10:20.924
It's true. In two days,

10:21.055 --> 10:22.839
the mayor is hand-picking
the next candidate.

10:22.970 --> 10:25.102
And if the rumors
of his fetish are true,

10:25.146 --> 10:28.236
he's also feet-picking.
[ Audience laughing ]

10:28.366 --> 10:31.848
You're -- You're being seriously
considered for public office?

10:31.979 --> 10:34.503
Absolutely!
I'm gonna be like --

10:34.634 --> 10:37.114
like an influencer,
but for politicking.

10:37.245 --> 10:40.117
[Chuckles]
What do you call that?

10:40.161 --> 10:42.337
Politician.
[ Audience laughing ]

10:42.467 --> 10:44.905
Oh.And -- And so
this election, it's --

10:45.035 --> 10:46.776
Here to stay, baby!

10:46.907 --> 10:50.954
Like that mole on my hip
that I refuse to get looked at.

10:50.998 --> 10:53.522
I nicknamed it Neil.
[ Audience laughing ]

10:53.653 --> 10:55.872
Speaking of,
where is Neil, anyway?

10:56.003 --> 10:59.180
Neil? Neil -- Neil?
Neil? Neil? Uh...

10:59.223 --> 11:00.529
[ Audience laughing ]

11:00.660 --> 11:02.574
Has he not been around?

11:02.705 --> 11:04.576
I just assumed
the world got quieter.

11:04.620 --> 11:05.926
[ Audience laughing ]

11:06.056 --> 11:08.537
It is a rough ride
clinging to coattails,

11:08.668 --> 11:12.410
but that is his job
as my best friend to hang on.

11:12.541 --> 11:13.934
Maybe I need
to go remind him of that

11:14.064 --> 11:15.762
in the form
of a purple nurple.

11:15.892 --> 11:16.980
Oh, no, no,
because, you know,

11:17.111 --> 11:19.766
Patty said that he got
food poisoning.

11:19.896 --> 11:23.900
I guess he has that one plate
that he uses over and over.

11:24.031 --> 11:25.597
Ah, yep, the blue one.

11:25.641 --> 11:27.077
[ Audience laughs ]

11:27.208 --> 11:29.689
Son, he's a distraction,
alright?

11:29.819 --> 11:31.168
We've got to get focused.

11:31.299 --> 11:33.954
Got to get serious.
You got to get thick shoes

11:34.084 --> 11:37.174
that won't be punctured
by stray needles.

11:37.305 --> 11:40.003
We're going to the vacant lot
to shoot this political ad!

11:40.134 --> 11:41.309
[Thud]Aah.

11:41.439 --> 11:44.181
Aw, man,
Neil is gonna be bummed.

11:44.312 --> 11:45.966
He loves that place.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.445
[ Audience laughs ]

11:47.489 --> 11:49.534
[ Laughter stops]

11:49.665 --> 11:55.279
♪

11:55.410 --> 11:57.325
[Door opens]

11:57.455 --> 12:01.851
♪

12:01.982 --> 12:05.115
[Sniffles]
I've never hurt him before.

12:05.246 --> 12:07.291
♪

12:07.422 --> 12:08.945
Hey.

12:09.076 --> 12:11.774
Hey, if you need a reminder
of what he did --

12:11.905 --> 12:13.776
♪

12:13.907 --> 12:15.125
Jesus.

12:15.256 --> 12:19.477
♪

12:19.608 --> 12:21.697
You were basically
saving my life.

12:21.828 --> 12:31.185
♪

12:31.315 --> 12:32.229
[Blood crackling]

12:32.360 --> 12:34.057
Oh, God.[Groaning loudly]

12:34.188 --> 12:36.190
Okay, we have to get him
to a doctor.

12:36.320 --> 12:37.974
What, what? What?

12:38.105 --> 12:39.759
That might be really bad.
I have no idea.

12:39.889 --> 12:41.586
No. Hey. Hey.

12:41.717 --> 12:44.285
He's awake. He's alert.

12:44.415 --> 12:46.591
Watching all of "ER"
does not make you a doctor.

12:46.722 --> 12:49.246
I don't like this situation
either, okay?

12:49.377 --> 12:51.379
But we can't let him out
until we know he'll be quiet.

12:51.509 --> 12:54.208
[Muffled yell]

12:54.338 --> 12:56.036
And how are we
gonna do that?

12:56.166 --> 12:57.864
I don't know.
I don't --

12:57.994 --> 13:00.257
Blackmail? I don't --
We'll figure it out, okay?

13:00.388 --> 13:02.172
No, no.

13:02.303 --> 13:04.044
[Whispering]
We have to do something now.

13:04.174 --> 13:05.262
Reason with him.

13:05.393 --> 13:06.611
Reason? With Neil?

13:06.742 --> 13:08.918
Yeah.
He's not a complete idiot.

13:09.049 --> 13:10.920
He just wants you
to think he is.

13:11.051 --> 13:12.052
Why?

13:12.182 --> 13:14.184
Because...then
you pay his rent

13:14.315 --> 13:16.099
and bail him out
for 30 years.

13:16.230 --> 13:18.449
♪

13:18.580 --> 13:20.974
Wait, wait. What --Trust me.

13:21.104 --> 13:22.802
This place is a vault.

13:26.022 --> 13:27.763
[Panting]

13:27.894 --> 13:29.417
Bitch.
Great start.

13:29.547 --> 13:32.812
Okay, okay.

13:32.942 --> 13:34.509
Neil.

13:37.381 --> 13:38.818
This is
a misunderstanding.

13:38.948 --> 13:41.211
A misunderstanding?Uh-huh.

13:41.342 --> 13:43.474
Um, hello?!

13:43.605 --> 13:45.520
You think I buy that I'm tied up
with a head wound

13:45.650 --> 13:47.565
'cause I, what,
heard you wrong?

13:47.696 --> 13:49.350
No. Yes.

13:49.480 --> 13:50.917
It's 'cause you were
choking Allison.

13:51.047 --> 13:52.701
No, no, no, you would've
just called the cops,

13:52.832 --> 13:54.616
not whatever the hell
this is.

13:54.746 --> 13:58.315
You tried to kill Kevin.

14:02.015 --> 14:03.146
Fine. No --

14:03.277 --> 14:05.366
Okay, but there were
circumstances,

14:05.496 --> 14:08.935
and it was a terrible momentary
thing, and it's over.

14:09.065 --> 14:10.893
It's done.

14:11.024 --> 14:13.113
Oh, like I'm just gonna
believe you?

14:13.243 --> 14:14.592
Look at what you did to me.

14:14.636 --> 14:15.985
Well, look
what you did to me.

14:16.116 --> 14:17.465
Oh, that's the same
as trying to kill someone?

14:17.595 --> 14:19.162
It's all bad, okay?

14:19.293 --> 14:21.904
And I can't believe
you helped her.

14:22.035 --> 14:24.733
I thought you were one of us,
but this?

14:24.864 --> 14:26.953
You're clearly nuts.

14:27.083 --> 14:29.738
I always knew
you'd take after Mom.

14:29.869 --> 14:31.653
Ow!You're a useless piece of shit

14:31.783 --> 14:32.915
just like Dad!Okay.

14:33.046 --> 14:34.308
You hear me?!Okay. Okay, okay.

14:34.438 --> 14:36.092
Ah! Ow!

14:36.223 --> 14:41.924
♪

14:42.055 --> 14:45.101
Neil.
Think about it.

14:46.450 --> 14:49.932
Kevin's, like,
running for public office.

14:50.063 --> 14:53.153
He's a public figure now.

14:53.283 --> 14:56.896
So it'd be suicide
for us to try anything.

14:57.026 --> 14:59.637
Right?

14:59.681 --> 15:00.551
Right?

15:00.682 --> 15:01.857
Yes, ri-- Yes.
Yes.

15:01.988 --> 15:04.251
Yes. Right.

15:04.381 --> 15:07.384
Okay. So you're done
trying to kill my best friend.

15:07.515 --> 15:09.909
Congrats.
You still tried once!

15:10.039 --> 15:11.954
[Doorbell rings]

15:12.085 --> 15:13.129
Who's --

15:13.260 --> 15:14.391
Help!!

15:14.522 --> 15:16.045
No! Oh! Shh, shh, shh!Help! Help!

15:16.176 --> 15:18.961
Shut up! Okay. Shut up,
shut up, shut up, shut up.

15:19.092 --> 15:20.310
You said
this place was a vault.

15:20.441 --> 15:22.530
It is, but now's not a good time
to test that.

15:22.660 --> 15:25.881
[Neil screaming, muffled]

15:26.012 --> 15:27.274
Hey.

15:27.404 --> 15:29.232
Hey.

15:29.363 --> 15:31.669
Isn't that
what you wore last night?

15:31.800 --> 15:33.758
Mm, yeah.

15:33.889 --> 15:35.717
I fell asleep on the couch.

15:35.847 --> 15:37.806
Just woke up.
Ah.

15:37.937 --> 15:39.982
Are you ready?Ready for...

15:40.113 --> 15:41.636
Don't you have
a couple porch chairs

15:41.766 --> 15:43.681
you Tom-Sawyered me
into putting together with you?

15:43.812 --> 15:46.206
Oh.I mean, you said "with."

15:46.336 --> 15:47.598
I assume you meant "for."

15:47.729 --> 15:49.426
[Chuckles]

15:49.557 --> 15:50.950
I'm -- I'm sorry.

15:51.080 --> 15:53.387
I, uh --
I completely spaced.

15:53.517 --> 15:56.781
The truth is, is I'm --
I'm not feeling very well.

15:56.912 --> 15:58.131
Oh, is that why
you slept on the couch?

15:58.261 --> 15:59.567
Yeah, mm-hmm.

15:59.697 --> 16:01.569
Sorry.
But you're in luck,

16:01.699 --> 16:03.832
because I heat up
chicken noodle soup real well.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.181
Mostly because
I add extra pasta --

16:05.312 --> 16:08.706
Soup sounds great,
but let's not be here.

16:08.837 --> 16:09.838
Let's go out.Are you sure?

16:09.969 --> 16:12.232
I mean, if you're sick --No, no.

16:12.362 --> 16:13.929
Going out will do me good.

16:14.060 --> 16:15.713
Fresh air and all that.

16:15.844 --> 16:18.020
Why don't you go keep warming
the car, and I'll --

16:18.151 --> 16:19.239
I'll be there
in a few minutes

16:19.369 --> 16:21.458
after I, you know...
pbht!

16:21.589 --> 16:24.679
I don't know. I kind of like
this look even more day two.

16:24.809 --> 16:26.159
Shut up. I'll be right out.I --

16:26.289 --> 16:31.033
♪

16:32.730 --> 16:34.428
[Groans]

16:34.558 --> 16:35.690
[Muffled] Help!
Shh!

16:35.820 --> 16:37.083
It's Tammy.[Muffled screaming]

16:37.213 --> 16:38.867
Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh!Shut up.

16:38.998 --> 16:40.477
Is she gone?

16:40.608 --> 16:42.479
[Sighs]
I-I told her I was sick

16:42.610 --> 16:43.741
and I'd go out
for soup or something.

16:43.872 --> 16:46.179
I don't know,
I think I blacked out.

16:46.309 --> 16:48.485
How the hell
am I dating a cop?

16:48.616 --> 16:52.011
Okay, no, no, it's good
to get her away from here, okay?

16:52.141 --> 16:54.622
So you keep her happy.
I'll stay here.

16:54.752 --> 16:56.493
Are you sure?

16:56.624 --> 16:58.147
I don't want to leave you
alone with him.

16:58.278 --> 17:00.062
It's fine, it's fine.
I'll -- I'll work on him.

17:00.193 --> 17:01.498
I'll try to fix it.

17:01.629 --> 17:03.631
Okay.
I'll be quick.

17:03.761 --> 17:05.024
Okay.

17:05.154 --> 17:07.461
[Muffled yell]Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

17:07.591 --> 17:08.636
Please.

17:08.766 --> 17:11.204
♪

17:11.334 --> 17:13.510
[Door opens, shuts]

17:13.641 --> 17:16.209
I really am sorry
about all this.

17:16.339 --> 17:18.167
No, I really am.

17:18.298 --> 17:20.430
I didn't know what to do.
It just got out of hand.

17:20.561 --> 17:25.827
♪

17:25.957 --> 17:31.137
♪

17:31.267 --> 17:33.008
[Sighs]

17:33.139 --> 17:42.409
♪

17:42.539 --> 17:45.542
What?

17:45.673 --> 17:48.110
Does Patty pay your rent?

17:48.241 --> 17:49.851
It was our parents' duplex.

17:49.981 --> 17:51.592
No, but the mortgage.

17:51.722 --> 17:54.116
She has to, right?
'Cause you can't hold down a job

17:54.247 --> 17:55.291
for more than
a couple of weeks.

17:55.422 --> 17:58.251
It's not my fault.
I get overwhelmed.

17:58.381 --> 18:00.557
Oh. Right.

18:02.646 --> 18:04.909
And everything else?

18:05.040 --> 18:08.913
Does Kevin pay
for everything else?

18:09.044 --> 18:09.958
[Scoffs]

18:10.089 --> 18:12.178
But how?

18:12.308 --> 18:15.572
I can't even get him
to put gas in his own car.

18:15.703 --> 18:17.183
He never does anything
I want him to.

18:17.313 --> 18:19.010
Why would he?

18:19.141 --> 18:23.189
You know how often
you say, "But, Kevin"?

18:23.319 --> 18:24.799
Okay.We made a drinking game

18:24.929 --> 18:27.367
out of it last St Paddy's day.
I blacked out.

18:27.497 --> 18:30.370
Well, you also took a header
off Turtle Boy,

18:30.500 --> 18:32.502
and Kevin laughed
till he puked,

18:32.633 --> 18:34.591
so it was a great day.

18:34.722 --> 18:39.161
You're always trying to make him
do stuff or not do stuff.

18:39.292 --> 18:41.163
But when has nagging him
ever worked?

18:43.470 --> 18:45.950
♪

18:46.081 --> 18:48.605
Never.

18:48.736 --> 18:50.738
[Breathes shakily]

18:50.868 --> 18:55.873
♪

18:56.004 --> 18:59.181
So that's why
you tried to kill him?

18:59.312 --> 19:01.270
'Cause he doesn't care
when you whine?

19:01.401 --> 19:08.756
♪

19:08.886 --> 19:10.627
[Sighs]

19:10.758 --> 19:13.587
Maybe he doesn't care
when I whine,

19:13.717 --> 19:16.416
but he laughs
when you bleed.

19:18.461 --> 19:19.810
Oh, come on.

19:19.941 --> 19:21.334
[Muffled grunt]

19:21.464 --> 19:25.207
♪

19:25.338 --> 19:27.166
Maybe someday
you'll see that.

19:27.296 --> 19:32.171
♪

19:35.348 --> 19:36.523
[Bell dings]Man: Order up.

19:36.653 --> 19:38.786
♪

19:38.916 --> 19:40.657
Isn't this place great?

19:40.788 --> 19:44.226
It has zero charm,
which is of course my type.

19:44.357 --> 19:50.189
♪

19:50.319 --> 19:52.843
Hey.

19:52.974 --> 19:54.193
You feeling okay?

19:55.977 --> 19:59.328
I'm sorry.
I, uh, um...

19:59.459 --> 20:03.027
I thought getting out of the
house would help, but maybe...

20:03.158 --> 20:05.204
maybe this was a bad idea.

20:05.334 --> 20:07.684
Were you up all night?

20:07.815 --> 20:09.643
Pretty much.

20:09.773 --> 20:11.035
Maybe I just go back
with you.

20:11.166 --> 20:12.472
No.

20:12.602 --> 20:15.214
No. It's fine.

20:15.344 --> 20:17.477
It's terrible being sick
and alone.

20:17.607 --> 20:20.262
I wasn't alone.
Allison came by a few times.

20:20.393 --> 20:21.481
Mm.

20:21.611 --> 20:24.223
[Indistinct conversations]

20:28.401 --> 20:31.230
I know you don't like her.

20:31.360 --> 20:33.319
But you don't really
know her.

20:33.362 --> 20:34.885
Do you?

20:35.016 --> 20:36.713
Know her or like her?

20:36.844 --> 20:38.411
Either.

20:38.541 --> 20:39.977
Yeah.

20:40.108 --> 20:41.849
I mean, it --

20:41.979 --> 20:43.894
it's just like
you with Bram.

20:44.025 --> 20:45.244
I don't get it at all,

20:45.374 --> 20:47.289
but you cut that guy
all kinds of slack.

20:47.420 --> 20:49.291
He's my partner.Yeah, and she and I

20:49.422 --> 20:50.945
are around each other a lot.

20:51.075 --> 20:54.383
We put up with
the same idiots all day.

20:54.514 --> 20:56.733
I don't know. I mean,
she looks out for me.

20:56.864 --> 20:58.692
I look out for her.

20:58.822 --> 21:00.607
If you say so.

21:00.737 --> 21:01.999
I do.

21:02.130 --> 21:06.526
♪

21:06.656 --> 21:08.397
[Bell dings]Order up.

21:08.528 --> 21:10.704
♪

21:10.834 --> 21:12.271
Excuse me.

21:14.011 --> 21:16.057
Oh, good, you're home.

21:16.187 --> 21:17.188
I need you
to look at something.

21:17.319 --> 21:18.799
No, I am not
doing that again.

21:18.929 --> 21:21.236
Just get a hand mirror and lift
your legs over your head.

21:21.367 --> 21:25.022
No, my dad just sent over the
rough cut of our political ad.

21:25.153 --> 21:28.809
I need the opinion of the...
uninformed public.

21:28.939 --> 21:30.506
Please sit.

21:30.637 --> 21:32.769
Kev, after what happened,

21:32.900 --> 21:34.554
isn't it a lot
to put ourselves through?

21:34.684 --> 21:36.164
It's not a lot, babe.

21:36.295 --> 21:37.687
It's only a 30-second ad.

21:37.818 --> 21:39.167
No, I mean this whole
election thing.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.125
It's -- It's --
It's too much.

21:41.256 --> 21:42.997
It's not too much,
I promise.

21:43.127 --> 21:44.346
We -- We'll fund-raise.

21:44.477 --> 21:45.695
It won't cost us a thing.

21:45.826 --> 21:46.957
But, Kevin!

21:47.088 --> 21:48.872
"But, Kev-i-i-in."

21:48.916 --> 21:50.221
[ Audience laughs ]

21:52.093 --> 21:53.616
Never mind.

21:53.747 --> 21:54.922
Let's watch the ad.

21:55.052 --> 21:57.011
Yeah?Yeah.

21:57.054 --> 21:59.230
[ Patriotic music playing ]
[on TV] Hi, I'm Kevin McRoberts,

21:59.274 --> 22:02.277
everyday hero.
And I, Kevin McRoberts,

22:02.321 --> 22:04.279
am running for City Council.

22:04.323 --> 22:08.065
That's Kevin McRoberts --
K-E-V-I-N,

22:08.109 --> 22:10.285
big "M," little "c," big "R,"

22:10.329 --> 22:12.766
little "o," little "b,"
little "e" --

22:14.420 --> 22:15.725
Why'd you pause it?

22:15.856 --> 22:17.988
You didn't watch me
finish spelling.

22:18.119 --> 22:20.643
Well, I know how it ends.

22:20.774 --> 22:23.777
I'm -- I'm just worried
that this ad, it --

22:23.907 --> 22:25.909
it isn't you.

22:26.040 --> 22:29.783
How do you mean? Dad says
it's all about name recognition.

22:29.913 --> 22:32.351
That's my name.

22:32.481 --> 22:34.527
No, I mean
it just doesn't...

22:34.657 --> 22:37.312
capture how awesome
you really are.

22:37.443 --> 22:38.618
Bro.

22:38.661 --> 22:41.360
[ Audience laughs ]

22:41.490 --> 22:44.363
Call me
absolutely insane...

22:44.493 --> 22:46.843
but you might
actually be right!

22:46.974 --> 22:49.019
You know, when Dad
was story-boarding it out,

22:49.150 --> 22:50.412
I did feel a little --

22:50.543 --> 22:52.371
Like a -- Like a weenie
little pansy boy

22:52.501 --> 22:54.808
got dressed up by his daddy.Okay, okay.

22:54.938 --> 22:58.202
You need to show your voters
who you really are,

22:58.333 --> 23:02.424
your authentic...
kickass self,

23:02.555 --> 23:06.863
and they'll
remember you forever.

23:06.994 --> 23:09.300
Forever?

23:09.431 --> 23:13.435
Or at least
until they vote.

23:13.566 --> 23:15.698
Yeah, but how would we
finish it in time?

23:15.829 --> 23:20.007
The ad's due to Local Access 37
by tomorrow.

23:20.137 --> 23:21.487
I'll help you.

23:21.617 --> 23:23.663
Last time you said that,
you grabbed the wheel,

23:23.793 --> 23:27.231
and I crashed
into a fire hydrant.

23:27.362 --> 23:29.756
Instead of
a crowd of children.

23:29.799 --> 23:32.019
[ Audience laughs ]

23:32.149 --> 23:34.238
That's it. It's settled.

23:34.369 --> 23:35.501
You and me, babe,
we are gonna

23:35.631 --> 23:37.720
Oh.make a political ad together!

23:37.851 --> 23:40.897
Okay.Let's get our
creative juices flowing.

23:41.028 --> 23:43.073
Okay, okay,
let's brainstorm.

23:43.204 --> 23:45.206
Oh, no, no, that's what
I call pounding beers

23:45.336 --> 23:47.034
and ripping shots.
[Laughs]

23:47.164 --> 23:48.905
Of course.

23:49.036 --> 23:51.038
[Pounds chest]
I'm in.

23:51.168 --> 23:53.562
Yes! Here you go.

23:53.693 --> 23:57.697
Let's introduce this town to
the authentic Kevin McRoberts.

23:57.827 --> 23:59.394
[Laughs]

23:59.438 --> 24:02.528
[ Audience laughing ]

24:02.658 --> 24:05.487
And this time,
they're staying down!

24:05.531 --> 24:07.837
[ Audience laughs, applauds ]

24:07.968 --> 24:08.969
Patty: Allison?

24:09.099 --> 24:11.493
♪

24:11.624 --> 24:13.364
Allison?

24:23.679 --> 24:24.724
What happened?
Where's Allison?

24:24.854 --> 24:26.116
She ran out of here
right after you.

24:26.247 --> 24:27.814
She did? Why?

24:27.944 --> 24:31.557
She's with Kevin, probably
trying to kill him again.

24:31.687 --> 24:33.863
What the hell
is she thinking?

24:33.907 --> 24:37.301
What the hell
are you thinking?

24:37.432 --> 24:40.566
No.

24:40.696 --> 24:42.002
Don't start.

24:42.132 --> 24:43.873
Don't start that
guilt-tripping crap.

24:44.004 --> 24:45.745
Oh, it's crap?

24:45.875 --> 24:47.181
Look at all this.

24:47.311 --> 24:48.922
Ugh.I don't know why I'm bothering

24:49.052 --> 24:52.621
to try and make you care,
because she won't let me go,

24:52.752 --> 24:54.928
and you do what she says,
no questions asked.

24:55.058 --> 24:57.104
That's not true.Oh, please.

24:57.234 --> 24:59.410
I've been watching
you two.

24:59.541 --> 25:02.326
She says "we" all the time
like you're in this together,

25:02.457 --> 25:05.504
but, Patty, where is she?

25:05.634 --> 25:08.855
You do the work,
and she calls the shots.

25:08.898 --> 25:11.901
So why waste my time trying
to get you to help me, Trish?

25:12.032 --> 25:14.034
Don't call me that.

25:14.164 --> 25:17.690
But Lisa Fazzolari called you
that your entire junior year.

25:17.820 --> 25:19.518
That girl kept failing
her driver's test,

25:19.648 --> 25:21.868
and you'd chauffeur
her everywhere,

25:21.998 --> 25:23.957
once to a party that you weren't
even invited to, right?

25:24.087 --> 25:25.349
Shut up.

25:25.480 --> 25:27.351
You just sat outside
keeping the car warm,

25:27.482 --> 25:29.353
but this is
even more pathetic.

25:29.484 --> 25:35.534
♪

25:35.664 --> 25:38.188
I don't care what you think.

25:38.319 --> 25:40.451
You had your hands on her.

25:40.582 --> 25:42.628
What excuse could you
possibly have?

25:42.758 --> 25:44.673
It was an accident.
Every report card I ever got

25:44.804 --> 25:45.805
said I don't know
my own strength.

25:45.935 --> 25:47.371
And it was bullshit then.

25:47.502 --> 25:49.765
She tried to kill someone.

25:49.896 --> 25:52.289
♪

25:52.420 --> 25:53.726
I could argue it was
self "offense."

25:53.856 --> 25:56.772
Oh, God. Just stop.

25:56.903 --> 25:59.383
Jesus.

25:59.514 --> 26:02.038
She's...

26:02.169 --> 26:04.388
That is no victim.Neil.

26:04.519 --> 26:06.608
Neil. [Scoffs]

26:06.739 --> 26:08.392
[Exhales sleepily]

26:08.523 --> 26:12.353
♪

26:12.483 --> 26:13.572
Neil.

26:27.542 --> 26:32.895
♪

26:32.939 --> 26:38.161
♪

26:38.292 --> 26:39.989
Patty?

26:40.120 --> 26:41.208
No, no, no.

26:41.338 --> 26:43.079
♪

26:43.210 --> 26:44.777
Patty! Oh.

26:44.907 --> 26:46.822
♪

26:46.953 --> 26:48.824
Patty?

26:48.955 --> 26:50.347
Patty!

26:50.478 --> 26:53.568
♪

26:53.699 --> 26:55.352
What happened?
Did he get out?

26:55.483 --> 26:57.224
No.

26:57.354 --> 26:59.269
I let him out.

26:59.400 --> 27:02.098
What are you talking about?I brought him to the hospital.

27:02.229 --> 27:04.144
W-Why?
I had to.

27:04.274 --> 27:06.668
Whatever happens, happens,
but having him sedated in there

27:06.799 --> 27:08.539
is better than
dead in my basement.

27:08.670 --> 27:10.367
Well, I didn't want him dead
in your basement, either,

27:10.498 --> 27:13.457
but we could have found
another way.

27:13.588 --> 27:14.894
Why didn't you trust me?

27:15.024 --> 27:16.852
I couldn't wait for you
to realize this is serious.

27:16.983 --> 27:18.767
Oh, you think
I don't know that?

27:18.898 --> 27:21.291
I didn't want to hurt him.
I didn't want any of this.

27:21.422 --> 27:24.120
But also --
Stop showing off the bruise.

27:24.251 --> 27:26.732
Yes, Neil did that,

27:26.862 --> 27:28.908
but you're not just
some victim.

27:29.038 --> 27:30.910
He's gonna talk
when he wakes up.

27:31.040 --> 27:32.259
Maybe he should.

27:32.389 --> 27:33.564
What?

27:35.654 --> 27:38.091
I hope not.

27:38.221 --> 27:42.051
And I'll figure something out,
but I'll figure it out alone.

27:42.182 --> 27:44.358
You don't have to
figure it out alone.

27:46.490 --> 27:48.057
Why did you leave?

27:48.188 --> 27:50.320
You left Neil
in the basement.

27:50.451 --> 27:52.453
What were you doing
with Kevin tonight?

27:56.675 --> 27:58.502
After everything
that's happened,

27:58.633 --> 28:00.069
you're still trying
to kill him?

28:00.200 --> 28:03.812
No, I just -- I can't have him
in this election.

28:03.943 --> 28:06.467
Can you imagine him in any
position of power? Come on.

28:06.597 --> 28:09.949
I'm not an idiot, okay?

28:10.079 --> 28:11.385
Don't you just assume
that I'll go along

28:11.515 --> 28:12.734
with whatever you say,
on your side,

28:12.865 --> 28:14.388
no questions asked.

28:16.303 --> 28:18.958
You want him out so that you can
try to run him over

28:19.088 --> 28:21.482
or force feed him Oxys
and no one will care.

28:21.612 --> 28:24.964
He'll be --
He'll be nobody.

28:25.094 --> 28:27.618
Patty, I'm sorry, okay?

28:27.749 --> 28:29.708
But I had to do this tonight.

28:29.838 --> 28:32.058
And it's done, I think.

28:32.188 --> 28:34.234
So I am here.

28:34.364 --> 28:37.759
I'm not gonna make you try to
figure this out by yourself,
okay?

28:37.890 --> 28:40.196
I really, I --
I am here.

28:43.896 --> 28:46.333
No.

28:46.463 --> 28:48.465
No, you're not.

28:48.596 --> 28:49.771
Not anymore.

28:51.991 --> 28:54.515
Just take care of yourself,
alright?

28:54.645 --> 28:56.082
And I'll do the same.

28:56.212 --> 29:06.179
♪

29:06.309 --> 29:08.921
[Siren wailing]

29:09.051 --> 29:17.538
♪

29:17.668 --> 29:26.025
♪

29:26.155 --> 29:27.591
[Exhales heavily]

29:27.722 --> 29:33.423
♪

29:33.554 --> 29:35.425
Dad, Allison, come in here!

29:35.556 --> 29:37.863
The ad airs
in like 30 seconds!

29:37.993 --> 29:40.779
I'm exhausted, I'm hungover,
and this is all I'm living for.

29:40.909 --> 29:42.171
I thank you
for your support.

29:42.302 --> 29:44.652
I'm so excited.
My pulse is racing.

29:44.783 --> 29:46.567
Have 911 pre-dialed.

29:46.697 --> 29:48.656
Shoot,
I wanted to tape this.

29:48.787 --> 29:49.962
Oh, no. Don't worry.
I called the station.

29:50.092 --> 29:51.485
The campaign
bought 40 spots.

29:51.615 --> 29:53.226
They'll be airing
over and over all day.

29:53.356 --> 29:54.227
Shh, shh, shh.

29:54.357 --> 29:56.490
My ad is on.

29:56.533 --> 29:57.752
Wild Dude!

29:57.796 --> 29:59.928
[ Imitating electric guitar ]

29:59.972 --> 30:02.365
He is a cool dude.

30:02.409 --> 30:04.672
[ Imitating electric guitar ]

30:04.715 --> 30:06.892
He shoots the bad dudes.

30:06.935 --> 30:08.850
[ Imitating electric guitar ]

30:08.894 --> 30:11.026
The Worcester Wild Dude!

30:11.157 --> 30:12.723
Is that the mayor?Yeah.

30:12.854 --> 30:16.336
Yeah. I heard that he plays
darts, and Allison thought

30:16.466 --> 30:18.294
that this might signal to him
that we could be bros.

30:18.425 --> 30:20.340
Bros, yeah, bros.

30:20.383 --> 30:22.516
The Worcester Wild Dude!

30:22.559 --> 30:24.561
[ Imitating electric guitar ]

30:24.605 --> 30:26.650
[ Audience laughing ]

30:26.781 --> 30:27.869
Where the hell is my ad?

30:28.000 --> 30:31.307
Uh, scrapped
for authenticity.

30:31.438 --> 30:33.919
[Sighs]
That was awesome.

30:34.049 --> 30:35.921
Now I guess
we just, uh, sit back

30:36.051 --> 30:39.881
and wait for my political
star to rise.

30:40.012 --> 30:42.275
Kevin, what happened
to messaging?

30:42.405 --> 30:44.538
Assertive pointing?
Name recognition?

30:44.668 --> 30:48.281
Uh, Dad, I'm pretty sure people
will remember me after that.

30:48.411 --> 30:49.717
[Laughs]

30:49.848 --> 30:52.024
You didn't say
your real name once!

30:52.154 --> 30:54.504
[Cellphone ringing]

30:54.635 --> 30:56.158
[Gasps]
It's the mayor.

30:56.289 --> 30:58.769
Uh, excuse me
while I retire to my office.

30:58.900 --> 31:02.208
Kevin "Worcester Wild Dude"
McRoberts at your service.

31:02.251 --> 31:04.297
[ Audience laughing ]

31:04.427 --> 31:07.561
I knew I should have stayed out
of politics after Whitewater.

31:07.691 --> 31:09.345
The Clinton scandal?

31:09.476 --> 31:11.086
No, I went rafting
with Gerald Ford.

31:11.217 --> 31:13.175
The boat flipped. I had to
give him mouth-to-mouth.

31:13.219 --> 31:15.308
[ Audience laughing ]

31:15.438 --> 31:17.484
[Groans loudly]

31:17.614 --> 31:19.312
What's up?I'm out of the race.

31:19.442 --> 31:20.313
No!

31:20.443 --> 31:22.315
No...

31:22.445 --> 31:25.535
And he's filing
a restraining order against me.

31:25.666 --> 31:27.929
Just like Jeff Probst did
against Neil.

31:28.060 --> 31:31.585
Ugh, they booted me
from my destiny.

31:31.715 --> 31:34.240
You nailed the mayor
in the eye!

31:34.370 --> 31:36.895
[Laughing]

31:37.852 --> 31:40.159
[Breathes shakily]

31:53.868 --> 31:56.088
[ Phone line ringing]

31:56.131 --> 31:58.612
Diane: Hello?
Diane? Hi. [Chuckles]

31:58.742 --> 32:02.572
We are going to the Seas, and I
am buying you a bunch of drinks,

32:02.703 --> 32:06.098
because...maybe
this is a win for you.

32:06.228 --> 32:08.491
♪

32:08.535 --> 32:10.537
[ Indistinct announcements
over P.A. ]

32:10.667 --> 32:12.713
[Monitor beeping]

32:12.843 --> 32:18.110
♪

32:18.240 --> 32:21.113
[Groggy] They tried to kill him.
Can you believe?

32:21.243 --> 32:24.812
♪

32:24.943 --> 32:27.162
Bitches tried
to kill me, too.

32:27.293 --> 32:29.164
♪

32:29.295 --> 32:31.427
You're fine.
Everything's fine.

32:31.558 --> 32:33.342
[Chuckles]

32:33.473 --> 32:41.089
♪

32:41.220 --> 32:48.836
♪

32:53.014 --> 32:55.538
I've never seen you
drink like this.

32:55.582 --> 32:56.713
Like I'm having fun?

32:56.844 --> 32:59.020
[Scoffs]
Like there's no tomorrow.

33:00.413 --> 33:02.719
Okay, what -- what are we
toasting to again?

33:02.850 --> 33:05.157
[Rock music playing]

33:05.287 --> 33:07.333
Feminism?

33:07.463 --> 33:09.465
Feminism?

33:09.596 --> 33:11.554
I don't know.
Or something.

33:11.685 --> 33:14.427
Oh, la-di-da.

33:14.557 --> 33:17.430
I didn't realize you were busy
changing the world.

33:17.560 --> 33:19.171
I'm not.

33:19.301 --> 33:23.436
But I did something,
and it feels amazing.

33:23.566 --> 33:25.307
Mm-hmm.

33:25.438 --> 33:26.830
I just need
to focus on that

33:26.961 --> 33:29.964
before everything else
just crumbles to the ground,

33:30.095 --> 33:31.052
you know?

33:31.183 --> 33:33.272
Mm-hmm.

33:33.402 --> 33:34.708
D!

33:34.838 --> 33:39.278
This whole Chuck thing,
you're better off, okay?

33:39.408 --> 33:42.585
You're never gonna have to look
at another open cabinet again.

33:42.716 --> 33:44.544
Not just the cabinets.

33:44.674 --> 33:49.549
The back door, the bathroom
vanity, the dishwasher.

33:49.679 --> 33:53.031
I could have tripped over that
and broken my neck, you know?

33:53.161 --> 33:56.077
But he couldn't
be bothered.

33:56.208 --> 34:02.214
22 years, I spent closing stuff
behind that man.

34:02.344 --> 34:06.218
No, D, this isn't sad.

34:06.348 --> 34:08.307
This is like
when someone dies,

34:08.437 --> 34:11.919
but they're really old,
so it's fine.

34:12.050 --> 34:14.313
This isn't a funeral,
it's a celebration.

34:14.443 --> 34:18.273
Yeah. Yes.

34:18.404 --> 34:21.755
But I've been Mrs. Charles
McAnte for so long,

34:21.885 --> 34:26.673
it's like -- it's like
I like cleaning up after him,

34:26.803 --> 34:29.110
because I don't know
what I did before.

34:29.241 --> 34:30.981
[Indistinct conversations]

34:31.112 --> 34:35.682
Well, you -- you were
a whole other person.

34:35.812 --> 34:39.947
And you'll
find her again, okay?

34:40.078 --> 34:42.471
Just need a few more wins.

34:42.602 --> 34:43.690
Hmm.

34:43.820 --> 34:46.475
Hey, is that Kevin?

34:46.606 --> 34:48.912
It's on again.
Turn it up.

34:49.043 --> 34:50.653
It -- It is. It's Kevin.

34:50.697 --> 34:52.307
Kevin: Wild Dude!
Bar patrons: "Wild Dude!"

34:52.438 --> 34:54.179
[All imitating electric guitar]

34:54.309 --> 34:56.920
What?All: "He shoots the bad dudes."

34:57.051 --> 34:59.097
[All imitating electric guitar]

34:59.140 --> 35:00.881
"He is a cool dude."
Kevin: He is a cool dude.

35:01.011 --> 35:03.971
No, no, no, no.

35:04.014 --> 35:07.017
"The Worcester Wild Dude!"
The Worcester Wild Dude!

35:07.148 --> 35:11.500
Why is your husband on TV, huh?[Laughter, cheering]

35:11.631 --> 35:13.502
Your husband's
the Worcester Wild Dude?

35:13.633 --> 35:15.156
Yeah.That's awesome!

35:15.287 --> 35:18.551
Okay. Okay, uh,
how do you know this ad?

35:18.681 --> 35:20.553
Oh, it's been airing
over and over all day.

35:20.683 --> 35:22.207
Then News Channel 12
picked it up.

35:22.337 --> 35:24.557
I heard it made it over
to Channel 6 out of Boston.

35:24.687 --> 35:25.862
[Laughs]

35:25.993 --> 35:27.255
Why?

35:27.386 --> 35:29.301
It's hilarious.
I heard he's gonna be

35:29.431 --> 35:31.607
over at Kelly's Bar tomorrow,
singing the song live.

35:31.738 --> 35:33.522
[Laughs] Allison?!

35:33.653 --> 35:35.263
Kevin's famous!

35:35.394 --> 35:38.136
[Fading, echoing] Oh. Okay,
that is worth celebrating.

35:38.266 --> 35:40.268
I mean, I bet
Kevin never forgets

35:40.312 --> 35:42.662
to close a cabinet
behind him,huh?

35:42.792 --> 35:45.012
The only time
Chuck ever made the news

35:45.143 --> 35:46.448
was during
the blackout of '03

35:46.579 --> 35:49.451
when he looted
that dollar store, but Kevin?

35:49.495 --> 35:50.713
Kevin: Cheers, everybody!

35:50.757 --> 35:52.367
Kevin and Pete:
Everyday Hero!

35:52.498 --> 35:54.195
Put another win
on the board!

35:54.239 --> 35:55.718
Allison:
The world revolves around him.

35:55.762 --> 35:58.547
No, it's not that it does,
it's that it has to.

35:58.591 --> 35:59.766
Allison: No one deserves
what's coming to them

35:59.809 --> 36:01.376
more than that asshole.

36:01.507 --> 36:02.725
Yeah!

36:02.769 --> 36:04.510
Allison:
It's why he always wins.

36:04.553 --> 36:05.989
[ Laughter echoing]

36:06.120 --> 36:07.556
[Allison groans]

36:07.687 --> 36:11.560
♪

36:11.691 --> 36:13.083
[Sighs]

36:13.214 --> 36:16.783
♪

36:16.913 --> 36:18.698
Ugh.

36:18.828 --> 36:22.223
♪

36:22.354 --> 36:24.182
[Chuckles]

36:24.312 --> 36:25.487
Shoot.

36:25.618 --> 36:31.841
♪

36:40.241 --> 36:42.374
["I'm Shipping Up to Boston"
ringtone plays]

36:42.504 --> 36:46.595
♪

36:46.726 --> 36:48.249
[Tires screech]

36:53.950 --> 36:58.172
Glad you went in a ditch
'stead of hitting anyone else.

36:58.216 --> 37:02.045
The guys at the scene told me
you...fell asleep at the wheel?

37:02.089 --> 37:05.179
[ Indistinct announcements
over P.A. ]

37:05.310 --> 37:08.922
Your husband a cop
or something?

37:09.052 --> 37:11.011
Or something, yeah.

37:11.141 --> 37:13.187
Must be nice.

37:13.318 --> 37:18.975
♪

37:19.106 --> 37:24.851
♪

37:24.981 --> 37:27.941
Patty:
What happened to you?

37:28.071 --> 37:29.551
Got in an accident.

37:29.682 --> 37:32.250
♪

37:34.164 --> 37:35.818
How do I
make this better?

37:35.949 --> 37:38.865
♪

37:38.995 --> 37:41.781
Maybe you can't.

37:41.911 --> 37:44.653
You didn't do this
on your own.

37:44.784 --> 37:47.439
I hit him first.

37:47.569 --> 37:49.354
At least now you're
free to focus on

37:49.484 --> 37:53.488
whatever you're...
doing to Kevin.

37:53.619 --> 37:56.317
[Sighs]

37:56.448 --> 37:58.145
I made it worse.
[Scoffs]

37:58.276 --> 38:00.887
What?
Yeah, um...

38:01.017 --> 38:02.715
Somehow I made him famous?

38:04.804 --> 38:06.153
Got out of a DUI tonight

38:06.284 --> 38:08.024
because the cops found out
I was his wife.

38:08.155 --> 38:10.331
Wait.

38:10.462 --> 38:13.682
You drove drunk?

38:13.813 --> 38:16.511
What were you thinking?

38:16.642 --> 38:17.991
I can't leave.

38:18.121 --> 38:19.732
I can't kill him.

38:19.862 --> 38:22.517
I'm stuck here like this
until I die,

38:22.648 --> 38:24.867
and that's if I'm lucky.
That's if Neil doesn't talk

38:24.998 --> 38:27.914
and Nick -- you know.

38:28.044 --> 38:30.395
So...

38:30.525 --> 38:32.310
Why not get drunk
and drive my car?

38:36.531 --> 38:39.317
Allison?

38:39.447 --> 38:41.319
This self-destructive
bullshit?

38:43.495 --> 38:45.497
Killing yourself?

38:45.627 --> 38:48.064
It's just playing
the victim again.

38:48.195 --> 38:53.940
♪

38:54.070 --> 39:00.207
♪

39:02.644 --> 39:03.906
[Cackles]

39:04.037 --> 39:06.605
Good morning!

39:06.735 --> 39:09.390
Good morning.
[Laughs]

39:09.521 --> 39:12.175
I said, "Good morning."
[Laughs]

39:12.306 --> 39:13.176
Is it?

39:13.307 --> 39:15.657
Of course it is.

39:15.788 --> 39:18.312
I thought I was out.
I thought I was down.

39:18.443 --> 39:21.010
But instead,
I'm a celebrity!

39:21.141 --> 39:23.752
Oh, God,
I'm like a taste-maker.

39:23.883 --> 39:25.450
I'm practically
the ninth Wahlberg.

39:25.580 --> 39:27.539
[Laughs]

39:27.669 --> 39:29.367
You always
find a way to win.

39:29.497 --> 39:30.846
[Sighs]
And fix your face,

39:30.977 --> 39:34.067
'cause you're winning
by proxy.

39:34.197 --> 39:37.070
Right, like my face
is the problem.

39:37.200 --> 39:40.813
Oh, and, uh,
as Mrs. Worcester Wild Dude,

39:40.943 --> 39:43.032
you should
get a lot of cred,

39:43.163 --> 39:44.991
which you need
after word got out

39:45.121 --> 39:48.821
that you ordered Starbucks
over Dunkie's that one time.

39:48.951 --> 39:52.259
But hey, I got a big, uh,
photoshoot this afternoon,

39:52.390 --> 39:54.392
and I want you there
with me, baby.

39:54.522 --> 39:55.523
I don't want
to be in photos.

39:55.654 --> 39:58.221
Oh, no, I mean like
to cheer me on.

39:58.352 --> 40:01.399
What do you think?

40:01.529 --> 40:03.531
I think I'd rather
fake my own death.

40:03.575 --> 40:05.925
[ Audience laughing loudly]

40:05.968 --> 40:07.666
[ Applause]

40:10.277 --> 40:19.286
♪

40:19.417 --> 40:21.244
[Cellphone vibrating]

40:21.375 --> 40:27.468
♪

40:27.512 --> 40:29.122
Patty: What?
[ Voicemail beeps ]

40:29.252 --> 40:32.517
Patty, I figured it out.

40:32.560 --> 40:35.433
Patty: Allison?

40:35.476 --> 40:39.088
This self-destructive
bullshit?

40:39.132 --> 40:41.351
Killing yourself?

40:41.395 --> 40:43.005
It's just playing
the victim again.

40:43.136 --> 40:47.923
♪

40:48.054 --> 40:50.752
Allison: Nick, your brother,
everything that's happened --

40:50.883 --> 40:52.493
I know what we're gonna do.

40:52.624 --> 40:54.713
♪

40:54.843 --> 40:56.454
Put it all on me.

40:56.584 --> 41:02.242
♪

41:02.372 --> 41:07.900
♪

41:08.030 --> 41:09.597
[Sighs]

41:09.728 --> 41:11.686
♪

41:11.817 --> 41:12.948
[Beep]

41:13.079 --> 41:14.472
God damn it!

41:16.604 --> 41:18.345
Allison:
I'm trying to fix this.

41:18.476 --> 41:20.913
I have
a longer-term solution.

41:21.043 --> 41:22.436
I meant it
when I said I'm out.

41:22.567 --> 41:23.524
Okay.

41:23.655 --> 41:24.873
[ Doorbell rings ]

41:25.004 --> 41:26.484
Hi.

41:26.614 --> 41:28.398
The electricity
is out at my place. Mwah.

41:28.529 --> 41:29.965
I'm just trying
to save up right now.

41:30.096 --> 41:32.577
Diane: Oh, yeah?
For what?

41:32.707 --> 41:34.274
Vacation.

41:34.404 --> 41:35.841
They discharged me early.

41:35.971 --> 41:37.669
Neil?
Kev!

41:37.799 --> 41:39.932
♪

41:40.062 --> 41:41.281
I gotta
tell you something.

41:41.411 --> 41:45.154
♪

41:46.634 --> 41:55.774
♪

41:55.817 --> 42:05.523
♪

42:05.653 --> 42:15.097
♪
